description: From to rake (out) hell (“to search through hell thoroughly”), in the sense of a person so evil or immoral that they cannot be found in hell even after an extensive search: see rake (“to search through (thoroughly)”). Compare rakeshame.

adjectives.description: rakehell (comparative more rakehell, superlative most rakehell)

entries.meaning: (archaic) A lewd or wanton person; a debauchee; a rake. [from 16th c.]
